storyInfo: In the time when Gododdin is shrouded in Londinium's strife, Quercus, landship intelligence officer, takes to her doctor's capacity in treating all the refugees who've fled here so far. One day, a man who claims to be the brother of Quercus's KIA comrade-in-arms shows up before her, and places his saber at Quercus's throat.

attributes.text: You will follow in the footsteps of those who sacrifice themselves, for they will show you that narrow way to life;
Charge forth, and devour the enemy alive!
You will not forget the faces of those who give their mortal time, for by them you will bolster your rattled courage;
The upright of you need not fear!
Take their treasure, furnish your rooms.
â€”Extract from a speech prior to one of Londinium's battles

attributes.content: Winter of 1098
Caladon City
Quercus!
attributes.name: Grani

attributes.content: For the last time, under order of the Caladon Mounted Police, you need to take a proper breather!
attributes.name: Grani

attributes.content: You're not allowed to take a step near the refugee camps for the next twenty-four hours.
attributes.name: Grani

attributes.content: Officer Grani.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Are you sure about denying a doctor's aid in these times?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Grani sought me out not long ago, hoping I could offer some simple medical help for refugees from Londinium.
But things very quickly got out of hand for us...
You haven't left the camp since the first day you came.
attributes.name: Grani

attributes.content: You need proper rest, now!
attributes.name: Grani

attributes.content: But you know as well as I do, they're in urgent need of plenty more than just food, water and clothing.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Most of the doctors in the city have already been enlisted, and the Duke's not interested in sparing much attention on this.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: He only agreed to shelter the refugees in one place out of fear they'd cause needless commotion.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Then what if you're pushed too far too...?
attributes.name: Grani

attributes.content: Who do I ask for help then?
attributes.name: Grani

attributes.content: Who do I ask to be your doctor?
attributes.name: Grani

attributes.content: Hm?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Are you underestimating me, the Druid doctor?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: I know my limits.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: I don't.
attributes.name: Grani

attributes.content: So I'm going to make sure you get a good night's sleep, even if I have to lock you up.
attributes.name: Grani

attributes.content: I'll be even less likely to sleep, then.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Who knows what could happen in twenty-four hours.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: This matter's closed for debate.
attributes.name: Grani

attributes.content: *sigh*...
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: This is no time for you to be playing the hero.
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: You again.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: The annoyance that always shows up at times like this to laugh at me.
It's not as if you'd change anything by being there every second of every minute.
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: You can't save all of them.
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: You know I don't listen to you.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: I've never considered myself a hero.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: I'm just doing all I can...
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Too many times, I've been too late to Felines laid deathly still on cardboard bedding, too late to examine whether it really was just fatigue.
And I can only force myself to watch on, helpless.
Helpless, tearful young children, going against the crowds driven by fear, only to disappear in the end into the earth's embrace.
All you can...
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: Does that make it any more bearable for you?
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: You can shut up now.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: And I won't exist if I don't talk?
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: You still aren't ready to admit itâ€”to admit how powerless you are.
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: You're scared. Scared of life vanishing in your hands.
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: Exactly like then.
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: It was different then!
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: It was different!
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: I don't have the time to bother with her.
I've got more important things to do.
Quercus?
attributes.name: Grani

attributes.content: Grani, there's something outside the city I need you to help me with, right now.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: You aren't getting me out of your face with excuses.
attributes.name: Grani

attributes.content: I'll be right here, watching over you.
attributes.name: Grani

attributes.content: I got hold of a shipment of urgent pharmaceuticals from Columbia. The mercenaries will be waiting for me outside Caladon early tomorrow.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: You're a Mounted Officer. The snatch squads won't suspect you once you're back in the city.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: You know how important these pharmaceuticals are.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Fine, but you're not to leave!
attributes.name: Grani

attributes.content: Gododdin's officers wouldn't turn a blind eye to a place as dangerous as a refugee camp.
They show up at irregular intervals, sniffing out every army deserter hiding within.
That, or...
Those who seem like army deserters.
Even if they're skin and bones.
Even if you hate hearing it, I'll keep saying it.
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: Is surviving really something worth celebrating to these people?
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: Suffering, starvation, blades, hostility, envy...
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: Every day, every hour, every second...
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: Death's not such a scary thing in comparison, is it?
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: The idea of those words coming from a doctor's mouth makes me want to vomit.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: But you're the doctor.
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: And I... am a Victorian soldier.
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: I renounced that identity forever ago.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: But you still remember.
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: It doesn't matter.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: The power's gone out.
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: The last night as quiet as this was...
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: Oh, yes, it was when you first asked me the same things.
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: What did I ask you?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Unblessed lives.
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: Unfearful deaths.
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: You posed those same questions to me.
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: In the darkness, I pick up on a familiar scent.
Forrest.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Do you remember now?
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: He's right here.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Forrest!
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: Wake up!
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: This was a meaningless battle.
I lost every one of my comrades-in-arms.
Aaargh!
attributes.name: Forrest

attributes.content: *cough* *cough*... Captain...
attributes.name: Forrest

attributes.content: I... I can't go on...
attributes.name: Forrest

attributes.content: Stay strong. Now's not the time to hesitate or fear.
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: You just have to get through these ruins, and we can make it out.
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: *cough* *cough*... Captain...
attributes.name: Forrest

attributes.content: Corporal Forrest!
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: I order you to stand!
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: I'll carry you.
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: He's too gravely wounded.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: The way she speaks is always so out of place and time, the cold-blooded pest.
Enough! I don't want to hear any more from you.
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: He is my soldier, and I will bring him back!
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: Bring him back?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: They're dead. They've been labelled heroes.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: The furnace is burning ever brighter.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Still more children are waiting to be thrown in.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: If you're idle enough to flap at me, you would do better finding some way to tend to his wounds!
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: I can constrict the bleeding, but it still won't be any use.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: I know you need him to make it back alive.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: You want to tear the veil away from the ones who started the fire, and make them stare their own evils in the face!
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: You want to dig back out this honor dressed like a poison apple by your raw hands, straight from the mouths of the children!
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Enough!
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: Yes! That is my selfishness!
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: But in the end, you'll return home alone.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Carrying all the festering blame.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Nobody will listen to your story.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Not the children back home. Legends of heroes are far more attractive than cruel reality.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Not the men at the pub. Because you haven't anything that could draw their attention.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Not the ones who started the fire. All they'll do is fault you for scattering sparks over their beloved carpets.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Enough! Enough! Enough!
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: You...
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: I said shut up!
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: Forrest...
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: So you remember my brother's name.
attributes.name: Unfamiliar Man

attributes.content: Seeing the man before me, I'm somewhat dazed.
But not because he's pointing a saber at my throat. Because he looks far too much like that child did.
He's been hiding here the whole time, away from everyone.
But he can't fool the earth.
I haven't told Grani, though.
I'd know you anywhere. It was you who brought back my brother's death notification.
attributes.name: Unfamiliar Man

attributes.content: But maybe you don't recognize us lot anymore.
attributes.name: Unfamiliar Man

attributes.content: I was watching you for days in the camp after I saw you, you know. But you never even noticed me.
attributes.name: Unfamiliar Man

attributes.content: So, you're a doctor now?
attributes.name: Unfamiliar Man

attributes.content: I saw that Feline burst into tears thanking you. I saw how the girl you saved was beaming ear to ear.
attributes.name: Unfamiliar Man

attributes.content: I bet you're happy, aren't you?
attributes.name: Unfamiliar Man

attributes.content: Bloody...! Son of a... bitch!
attributes.name: Unfamiliar Man

attributes.content: Howling, wailing, bawling...
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: The earth's sprawling roots are withered about this great land.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: These are all I hear...
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: And it chokes me.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: You must love it, bathing in atonement.
attributes.name: Unfamiliar Man

attributes.content: But my brother's dead!
attributes.name: Unfamiliar Man

attributes.content: To hell with your clear conscience, you self-righteous...!
attributes.name: Unfamiliar Man

attributes.content: What did you do?!
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: I did nothing, and I could do nothing.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Captain... just kill me.
attributes.name: Forrest

attributes.content: My leg's broken anyway. I don't want to come back to my mum in this state...
attributes.name: Forrest

attributes.content: And my little brother. He's always been so proud of me...
attributes.name: Forrest

attributes.content: And I hear, you know... soldiers who die in action earn better compensation money...
attributes.name: Forrest

attributes.content: See?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: For him, surviving is hardly something worth celebrating.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: And death doesn't seem so frightening after all.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Captain! Um...
attributes.name: Forrest

attributes.content: You must tell them, when you return, about me at my bravest!
attributes.name: Forrest

attributes.content: Heh, heh...
attributes.name: Forrest

attributes.content: I can't ruin my brother's image of me, after all.
attributes.name: Forrest

attributes.content: Heh. And here we are now...
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: He's become a model to you.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: He doesn't want to die.
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: He's just scared of surviving...
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: Do it, Captain.
attributes.name: Forrest

attributes.content: I know, see, without my leg... I'm nothing but rubbish.
attributes.name: Forrest

attributes.content: So...
attributes.name: Forrest

attributes.content: May as well be this way...
attributes.name: Forrest

attributes.content: Enough!
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: Don't say a word more!
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: Are you talking to me?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: May life endure.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Bastard!
attributes.name: Unfamiliar Man

attributes.content: What are you acting dumb for? Say something!
attributes.name: Unfamiliar Man

attributes.content: You're Forrest's younger brother, Michael.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: If I'm remembering right, you should be on the Londinium front lines, in the Duke of Gododdin's army, and not here.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: So...
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: That's right, I'm a deserter.
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: You can turn me in now if you want.
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: It must be of your own accord that you came looking for me.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: I would never have come to you if there was any other choice.
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: I'd prefer to believe that Forrest never died.
That he's standing in front of me right now.
But I could never fool myself.
You killed him.
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: I had no other choice.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: He begged for your mercy.
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: He found a peaceful passing.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: So you killed him!
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: Are you done?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: No!
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: Bastard! Bastard, bastard, bastard...!
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: If I was just able to kill you right here and now...!
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: So, what do you need of me?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: The captured deserters, including Michael's comrades-in-arms, are all locked up on the west face of Caladon.
He wants me to rescue them.
I want him to disguise himself as staff in my shop.
A flower shop.
A flower shop?
So while we were risking our lives on the front...
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: This is what those shitheads were up to.
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: A commemoration dinner?
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: A commemoration dinner.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Bastard! Bastard, bastard, bastard...!
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: And you just let it happen?
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: These flowers have been bartered for a blind eye to the refugees.
For basic supplies.
For necessary privileges.
For more than a single life.
With just these?
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: Not just.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: But it is with these flowers, yes.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: You just can't let go of that ridiculous fantasy.
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: I know exactly what I'm doing.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Nothing constitutes this 'refugee camp' except a bunch of toys flung at the children on a charitable whim.
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: Today, they can have you practicing your art and saving people, sheltering them all in a castle of sand.
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: But tomorrow, they can have you killing them, knocking the castle down, burying them all beneath the ochre dust.
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: As long as the refugees don't make too much of a scene, they'll let anything slide.
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: I'm a doctor.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: I'm not killing anyone.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: But what if someone else did it?
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: Then you should ask yourself what would a Victorian soldier would do, in times like that.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Then what if it ends up like Forrest again...
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: I'm begging you.
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: You've been scared, ever since your first day with the refugees.
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: That the war will continue, that life will no longer be worth looking forward to.
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: That life will no longer be valued.
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: You know these things are bound to happen.
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: And bound to happen more than once.
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: So what will you do, Dr. Quercus?
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: What now?!
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: They've got people manhunting right up ahead!
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: Bastard...!
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: Frankly, in the midst of the drab, muddy streets, faces worn all around, this many flowers naturally stands out like a sore thumb.
Don't panic.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: They won't come prying.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: But the snatch squads are smart. They won't try to get themselves into hassle.
After all, they know what kind of person would need so many fresh flowers for their evening occasion, don't they?
Oof...
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: Get a move on.
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: Are you still worried I'll turn you in?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: I've had my eye on you forever at the refugee camp. You don't seem like the sort.
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: So I'm willing to gamble.
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: You don't need to say anything. I know what I'm doing here.
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: It doesn't mean I trust you.
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: And I'll be clear, I can't stand you.
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: I just wanted to warn you, if you keep acting sneakily like that... you'll only draw the snatch squad in by yourself.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Don't need you telling me.
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: Settle down! What are you hollering for?!
attributes.name: Snatch Squad Soldier A

attributes.content: Fowl-hearted rubbish, the lot of them...
attributes.name: Snatch Squad Soldier A

attributes.content: Hey, don't you think it's stuffy in here? Can't catch my breath.
attributes.name: Snatch Squad Soldier B

attributes.content: And there's a sort of...
attributes.name: Snatch Squad Soldier B

attributes.content: Is that some kind of... scent?
attributes.name: Snatch Squad Soldier A

attributes.text: May the earth once again care for life tender...

attributes.content: Oi, look!
attributes.name: Snatch Squad Soldier A

attributes.content: The vents!
attributes.name: Snatch Squad Soldier A

attributes.content: What?!
attributes.name: Snatch Squad Soldier B

attributes.content: Is that... flowers?
attributes.name: Snatch Squad Soldier B

attributes.text: May the earth have mercy, that our lost children lay to rest in her bosom...

attributes.content: Urgh...
attributes.name: Snatch Squad Soldier A

attributes.content: Wha...
attributes.name: Snatch Squad Soldier B

attributes.content: Come out.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Let's find your comrades.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: I've never seen Arts like that before.
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: Just some of the tradition of home.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: So them few are...
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: They're unconscious, that's all.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: You have enough time to get the ones you want out of here.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Hmph...
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: I can guess what crosses Michael's mind for a split-second.
But he doesn't draw his saber, after all...
He really does miss his brother so much.
The wrong person, the wrong place, the wrong standing.
Michael?!
attributes.name: Bewildered Deserter

attributes.content: How did you get in?
attributes.name: Wasting Deserter

attributes.content: I'm here to save you.
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: Follow me!
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: Nice going!
attributes.name: Wasting Deserter

attributes.content: Who's that with you?
attributes.name: Bewildered Deserter

attributes.content: She's...
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: She's just assisting.
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: Let's go.
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: Wait!
attributes.name: Bewildered Deserter

attributes.content: These stupid manhunting buggers.
attributes.name: Bewildered Deserter

attributes.content: I'm gonna settle my score with them.
attributes.name: Bewildered Deserter

attributes.content: What are you doing?
attributes.name: Bewildered Deserter

attributes.content: Michael and I are here to rescue you.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Not to kill them.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Oh, piss off!
attributes.name: Wasting Deserter

attributes.content: You know what they've done?!
attributes.name: Bewildered Deserter

attributes.content: All too well.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Of course you know what they perpetrated in the refugee camp.
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: Why are you stopping these deserters from bumping off these scum?
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: Listen to yourself.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: You were interrogating me just a second ago.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Now you're champing at the bit to end others' lives yourself.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: On the most upstanding and reasoned grounds, of course.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Let me through!
attributes.name: Bewildered Deserter

attributes.content: No.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: We don't need to waste any time in here.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Then just let me sock him once.
attributes.name: Bewildered Deserter

attributes.content: Go on.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: What about all the rest shut in here?
attributes.name: Wasting Deserter

attributes.content: You breaking them out too?
attributes.name: Wasting Deserter

attributes.content: I have them release everyone.
I tell them the way out of the city.
And I lock all of the snatch squad inside the cells.
You saved them.
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: Let's go.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Before we put anyone on high alert.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: There's somewhere we need to go first.
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: It's where all our supplies and gear's buried.
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: Here...
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: Yes, I remember.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: This is the place.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Of course.
It's one I'm all too familiar with...
This is Forrest's grave.
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: My brother.
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: Of course I remember.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: It was by my own hands...
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: I buried him here.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: It doesn't make sense...
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: Bastard! Bastard, bastard, bastard...!
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: Argh! It just doesn't make any sense!
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: Why?!
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: You'll save all those camp refugees, no matter how bad they're hurt.
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: You'll get us away from the manhunters, straight through a locked-down city like it's nothing.
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: You even chose to spare that bloody bunch of snatchers, those shiteating arseholes.
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: So whyâ€”did you abandon my brother?!
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: Why didn't you save him?!
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: I was powerless to.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Lies?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Fine.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: I'll just tell him...
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: His brother was too badly wounded.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Tell him his mistakes in battle weren't my fault.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Tell himâ€”all the rotten consequences for this should fall on the idiots in the top brass.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Maybe that'll make it easier for him to bear.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: And that's how you reassure yourself?
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: You don't need to tell the truth.
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: It's easier to bear...
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: And that's why you chose to lie.
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: I haven't.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: And that's why you chose to murder.
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: I wouldn't.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Then WHAT did you do?!
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: Are you going to keep looking for excuses?!
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: Answer me!
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: Look at me!
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: Look at Forrest.
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: The battle was completely meaningless.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Our entire side was annihilated, save for your brother and I.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: What?
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: I tried to get him out, but his wounds were just too grave.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: So in the end...
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: I gave him a peaceful death.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: A peaceful death?
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: So you mean...
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: Yes. I killed him.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: That's all it is to you! Just those couple of words!!
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: Bastard! Bastard, bastard, bastard...!
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: You killed him?
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: Indeed.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: I couldn't bear to see him suffer any longer...
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: I didn't want to see him return home, to become a madman persecuted by war.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: No!
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: You're just saying what you want!
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: Michael has been gripping the handle of his saber ever since we left the shop, but he hasn't drawn it once from its sheath.
Until now. His saber is held tight, and pointed at me.
You can kill me.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: But I don't owe you the slightest thing for your brother's death.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: You killed him!
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: You killed your own comrade!
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: I did.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Nothing about what I've done is worthy of commendation.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: I murdered my own soldier.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: I did the one thing a doctor should never do.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: There is no fair justification for my actions.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: But it was a decision I had to make.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: You've said enough!
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: I won't forgive you for this!
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: But it's because of your brother that I saved you, too.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: You resemble him a lot.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: All of you do.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Children whose eyes have been covered.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Driven, tempted, coerced.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Shoulder to shoulder...
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Step after step...
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Filled with fervor... rushing to your deaths.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Never should death have been so lauded.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Life is to be celebrated.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: You have the right to choose life.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: The earth will eternally embrace the weary children.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: That is why I saved you.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: You know something? Every letter my brother sent back...
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: No matter what else, he'd always mention you.
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: He said you were a great captain and leader, never berating people at each turn like the rest did...
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: Said you looked after him so much...
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: I believe my brother wouldn't lie...
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: I believe...
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: You must have your reasons for doing what you did.
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: Thank you for saving me.
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: I'll live. I'll live on well.
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: I see Michael slowly hang his head.
I can sense the emotions, bottled in his heart all along.
These past few days have shown me how incredible you are.
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: Michael!
attributes.name: Wasting Deserter

attributes.content: What are you doing?!
attributes.name: Wasting Deserter

attributes.content: But I still can't bear it.
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: I'm sorry.
attributes.name: Michael

attributes.content: Won't you retaliate against this?!
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: You haven't retaliated either, have you?
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: He thrust wide.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Did he mean to?
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: It doesn't matter.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Hey. You won't even be angry?
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: It's not you who should be bearing this, after all.
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: You know you're a victim too. You're not the one to blame when these things happen.
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: What happened back then, regardless of who was right or wrong, means nothing now no matter how deep you probe.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Suffering, casualty, hostility, blades, envy... all cut us far adrift from the earth.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: And in that moment, we are all the victims.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: I just don't know what to say to you.
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: I'm sure Forrest hoped his brother would have a proper life to live.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: In that instant, he was reborn, and found his way back to the earth's sprawling roots.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: If we continue to persecute each other so...
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Letting hate drive hate...
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: We would do no service to their wishes.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Theirs?
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: Theirs.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: And soâ€”
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: This is the best account I can give him.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: And you needn't keep blaming yourself any longer.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Mm. Congratulations.
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: How nice for you.
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: You've finally managed to get yourself killed.
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: Are you really giving up, just like that?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: You're the doctor here.
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: And more than that, a Druid priest.
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: Will you give up on life?
attributes.name: Quercus?

attributes.content: I beg of you, take care of him for me.
attributes.name: Corinna

attributes.content: *cough* *cough*... I...
attributes.name: Corinna

attributes.content: Never should death have been so lauded.
Life is to be celebrated.
Mum...
attributes.name: Derlyn

attributes.content: Take the child out of here for now.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Almost every day brings new faces before me, but I still try to remember all their names. Life should not be abandoned like this without a trace.
Quercus! What theâ€”?!
attributes.name: Bitter Root

attributes.content: What's all the blood on you about?
attributes.name: Bitter Root

attributes.content: I'll fetch you a doctor right now.
attributes.name: Bitter Root

attributes.content: I am a doctor.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: And I was once a Victorian soldier.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Now I'm a Rhodes Island Branch Operator, and Rhodes Island Gododdin intelligence officer.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: They who suffer are hung up high.
Look! That's our hero!
So the busybodies below the scaffold loudly cheer.
The Doctor's headed for Londinium.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: They need our backing on the intelligence front.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: But you...
attributes.name: Bitter Root

attributes.content: I'm fine.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: I just took a quick trip to the refugee camp earlier.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Hero!
Hero!
The children chant in voices raised high.
But they notice not the looks of worry in their parents' eyes.
I'm lucky Grani isn't back yet. I know she wouldn't let it rest without learning every last detail.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: I hope everything's going smoothly on her end. Please let nothing trouble her.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: For now, I'd best pretend I'm asleep before it's too late...
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Another day's dusk.
But the night won't be long.
Quercus!
attributes.name: Grani

attributes.content: Did you get some proper rest?
attributes.name: Grani

attributes.content: Quercus.
attributes.name: Goldenglow

attributes.content: I'm here to see you.
attributes.name: Goldenglow

attributes.content: Good evening...
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: *cough* *cough*...
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Quercus!
attributes.name: Goldenglow

attributes.content: Look at you! You didn't listen to me, did you?
attributes.name: Grani

attributes.content: Grani, the twenty-four hours are almost up.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Then I'll ground you for another twenty-four!
attributes.name: Grani

attributes.content: You lie down for me, right now!
attributes.name: Grani

attributes.content: Quercus, you look in terrible shape.
attributes.name: Goldenglow

attributes.content: I'm fine. I'll be good.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: In fact, I've baked you some biscuits.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Death casts away the dead, and salivates for the living. The most fearful torment would not so easily indulge these friends who mind each other so, nor those relatives for whom relief comes with great difficulty.
May the earth forgive.
May life endure.
May...
Quercus!
attributes.name: Grani

attributes.content: Heheh.
attributes.name: Quercus
